    value: 고려 공민왕 때의 고승.
english:
  title: Record of the Hall of Truth of Lazy-Old Master at Songcheon Temple on Yongja Mountain in Cheongju
  author: Lee Saek
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The Hall of Truth of Lazy-Old Master stands where all sacred mountains and blessed lands keep their shrines. Long ago, the brush of Mokeun recorded how this sanctuary came to be. Now his disciple Gakyeon came again, saying: "On Yongja Mountain in Cheongju, there remains a stone Maitreya and a stone pagoda—truly a blessed place. I have traveled through villages and towns, meeting faithful men and women, gathering alms to build three chambers. In the eighth month of the year Musal, the work was completed. We have hung the portrait of our Lazy-Old Master within, while the monks dwell in rooms to the left and right. Thus do we tend the incense morning and evening, repaying the grace of our teacher." He then asked me to write this record.

    Who cannot write a record? Yet to inscribe the Hall of Truth of Lazy-Old Master is a task for one such as myself.

    I replied: "The Master's pagoda bears an inscription I composed by imperial command. For his Hall of Truth, I now write this record for his disciples. Between the Master and myself stretches a distance—I never had fortune to study at his feet. Yet should the Hall of Truth endure through my words, should future generations come to know the Master's name through my brush, then I who never sat in his presence shall have served him better than those who basked in his teachings yet left nothing when he passed. Is this fortune mine? Or the Master's? Or that of his disciples? Such meetings of cause and circumstance deserve only a knowing smile."

    Thus was it written.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Lazy-Old Master (懶翁) was a renowned Buddhist sage of the Goryeo period under King Gongmin.
